author: Stuart Tomlinson | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Hillsboro man stabbed during possible gang-related fight at Walnut Street Park
text:
Hillsboro police are investigating a possible gang-related stabbing early Wednesday morning.
Jose Arellano-Sanchez, 22, arrived at Providence St. Vincent Medical Center at 2:10 a.m. for treatment of at least four stab wounds, said Lt. Henry Reimann, Hillsboro police spokesman.
Before police arrived, Arellano-Sanchez was transported to OHSU Hospital where he later told police that he was riding his bicycle in the area of Walnut Street Park when a car pulled up alongside him.
Riemann said there was an exchange of hand signs and words between Arrellano-Sanchez and three men in the car. One of the men allegedly exited the car and started to fight with Arellano. A second man got out of the car and came at Arellano-Sanchez from behind, allegedly stabbing him multiple times.
Reimann said Arellano-Sanchez apparently knew one of the attackers, but refused to identify him.
The case is under investigation by the Washington County Inter-agency Gang Enforcement Team.
